comments.body:
Similarly to the discussion on https://github.com/bitcoin/bitcoin/pull/32521#discussion_r2095472966, it seems to me we could fail early by exiting if the first one is already too big:
```suggestion
        sigops += tx.vin[i].scriptSig.GetSigOpCount(/*fAccurate=*/true);
        if (sigops > MAX_TX_LEGACY_SIGOPS) {
            return false;
        }
```
or inversely, if this isn't performance critical, we can do the check at the very end instead, to speed up the happy path by not doing intermediary checks. 
```C++
        sigops += tx.vin[i].scriptSig.GetSigOpCount(/*fAccurate=*/true);
        sigops += prev_txo.scriptPubKey.GetSigOpCount(tx.vin[i].scriptSig);
    }

    return sigops <= MAX_TX_LEGACY_SIGOPS;
}
```

Is there any advantage to this in-between solution?

